  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Department of Health and Human Services has obligated $13.5B in federal contracts in FY2026 to date. The agency recorded 20,003 awards with an average award size of $676K, and obligations fell 36.5% year over year. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historical obligations were $34.3B in FY21, $33.4B in FY22, $33.4B in FY23, $29.9B in FY24, and $21.3B in FY25. In FY2026 to date spending is concentrated in information technology and professional services, with Computer Systems Design Services accounting for $2.3B and Other Computer Related Services accounting for $1.2B. Research and development and pharmaceutical manufacturing also appear among the top categories, including Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $793M and Pharmaceutical Preparation Manufacturing at $562M. The largest contractors by obligation in FY2026 to date include GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $660M and MANHATTAN TORCON A JOINT VENTURE at $492M. This snapshot reflects obligated contract totals through the current reporting period.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How have HHS contract obligations changed year over year?",
        "body": "Obligations were $34.3B in FY21, $33.4B in FY22, $33.4B in FY23, $29.9B in FY24, $21.3B in FY25, and $13.5B in FY26. Obligations fell 36.5% year over year into FY2026 to date. The FY2026 total of $13.5B is a partial fiscal year figure. The agency issued 20,003 awards in FY2026 to date with an average award size of $676K."
      },
      {
        "heading": "What are the main contract categories and top vendors in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The largest category by obligation is Computer Systems Design Services at $2.3B, followed by Other Computer Related Services at $1.2B and Administrative Management and General Management Consulting Services at $1.1B. Research categories and manufacturing appear in the top ten, including Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $793M, Research and Development in Biotechnology at $782M, and Pharmaceutical Preparation Manufacturing at $562M. The top vendors by obligation are GENERAL DYNAMICS INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY, INC. at $660M and MANHATTAN TORCON A JOINT VENTURE at $492M, with additional large obligations to ACACIA CENTER FOR JUSTICE ($266M) and BOOZ ALLEN HAMILTON INC ($262M)."
      }
    ]
  },
