      "q": "How much does Department of Health and Human Services spend on contracts?",
      "a": "HHS has obligated $13.5B in contracts in FY2026 to date. The agency recorded 20,003 awards with an average award size of $676K, and obligations fell 36.5% year over year; recent fiscal-year totals were $34.3B in FY21, $33.4B in FY22, $33.4B in FY23, $29.9B in FY24, and $21.3B in FY25."
